  <p><li><strong>Register to teach a class in <%= SITE_NAME %>.</strong> (blurb/register_new_class)</li></p>
    <ol>
      <li><%= link_to "Create an OpenStax Tutor account", new_user_registration_path %>, if you haven't already.</li>
      <li>Request an administrator add your class to the <%= link_to "Course Catalog", catalog_path  %> and give you instructor permissions. </li>
    </ol>
  <p><li><strong>Plan your class before adding any course materials to OpenStax Tutor.</strong> (blurb/plan_class)</li></p>
    <ol>
      <li>Plan what course materials, i.e. resources and exercises, you will assign to students.</li>
      <li>Ensure these course materials are hosted on <%= link_to "Connexions", "http://www.cnx.org" %> and <%= link_to "Quadbase", "https://www.quadbase.org" %>.</li>
      <li>Decide if you will partner with <%= SITE_NAME %> researchers to run an educational experiment in connection with your class. </li>
      <li>Organize and sequence related course materials into topics.</li>
      <li>Begin thinking about the assignments (homeworks and tests) you will assign via <%= SITE_NAME %>.</li>
      <li>Consider if you will set up any learning conditions for your assignments.</li>
    </ol>
  <p><li><strong>Set up your class.</strong></li></p>
